VENUS_SYSTEM_PROMPT was ~48.9K chars (~12.2K tokens), which alone exceeded
Groq free-tier gpt-oss-120b's 8K TPM ceiling before any dynamic content
(business context, history, founder message) was added -- meaning no call
could ever succeed on the free tier regardless of retry/shrink logic.

Compressed to ~26.7K chars (~6.7K tokens) by cutting repeated meta-commentary
explaining *why* each rule exists and consolidating duplicate examples, while
preserving every distinct behavioral rule: evidence-first hypothesis
comparison, context sufficiency gate (A/B/C), causal chain reasoning,
confidenceNote grounding tiers, decision-card full-scoring, retrieval-gated
precedents, founder-history override, self-check + counter-argument passes,
and the full JSON card schema.

This alone drops the prompt under the free-tier 8K TPM ceiling with margin,
independent of the Groq Developer tier upgrade in the next commit. Re-run
scripts/src/venus-provider-ab-test.ts against this prompt before relying on
it in production -- compression is inherently lossy and needs a human read
of real output, not just a token count.
